node.text: With arguably the biggest worldwide audience ever for a skate contest, last weekend's Summer Games Men’s Street Skateboarding event was a pressure cooker. We are extremely hyped to see Berrics regulars @yutohorigome, @kelvinhoefler, and @jaggereaton on the podium; it's been a long journey and their hard work had a historic impact. We've compiled some of these champions' best moments under the Berrics' roof for your enjoyment… Congratulations Champions! 🙌 #skateboardingisfun #berrics

node.title: Congratulations to the Men’s Street Skateboarding Champions

node.text: @yutohorigome - From Next New Wave, to Olympic Gold Medalist. 🥇 Yuto exploded onto the scene with an incredible style, versatility, and diverse bag of tricks that he effortlessly did down the heaviest stairs and handrails, along with insanely technical ledge tricks, and even spinning a 540 or two on very. The whole point of the Next New Wave series was to highlight the fresh faces of skateboarding who were going to be huge stars one day and boy did we hit the nail on the head when we featured Yuto. It’s amazing to look back at this video part and see how good Yuto was, and yet he continued to get better and better. Now, only 5 years later, Yuto is an Olympic Gold Medalist for Skateboarding. 🥇 Thank you for the progression and congrats on making Skateboarding history this weekend. 🙌 Congratulations Yuto!! #berrics #nextnewwave #skateboardingisfun

node.text: @jaggereaton just became an official Skateboarding Olympic Metalist but let’s not forget he’s an absolute beast in the streets!! 🇺🇸🥉 Jagger turned Pro for @theheartsupply last year (with this incredible part) but he’s been skating in Pro contests before he was even pro. He was the first ever skater to win Tampa PRO as an AM in 2018, after previously winning Tampa Am just a few years before in 2014. He was the youngest skater to compete in the X Games (at the time) at age 11, has skated against the world's best for almost a decade and absolutely kills in the streets. Yesterday, all of that experience, talent, and (above all) hard work has finally paid off as Jagger won the Bronze Medal for Men's Street Skateboarding in the Olympics, making him the first American skater to win an Olympic medal for Skateboarding. 🇺🇸🛹 Last year, we had the privilege of hosting Jagger's PRO PART for @theheartsupply and it’s so sick to see him go as hard in the streets as he does in contests. It’s been a pleasure to watch his career progress and we’re incredibly happy for his success. 🙌 Congratulations Jagger!! 🥉 @usaskateboarding #skateboardingisfun #berrics

node.text: “A few years back, I was introduced to this new talent, @yutohorigome from @micky_papa and the Blind squad. After seeing him skate for just one day, I knew this dude was going to be a superstar.  He was the only one doing the tricks he did and he did them with ease.  Soon after, we decided to film a ‘Recruit’ part. After shooting it, I told my team, ‘there is nooo way this is a Recruit part’, which had been reserved for amatuer skaters only.  THIS DUDE IS A PRO, this part is a BATTLE COMMANDER.” - @chaseingabor 🗣 We knew back in 2017 that Yuto was something special and was going to be a force to be reckoned with. Yesterday, he proved us all right by becoming the worlds first Olympic Street Skateboarding Gold Medalist! 🥇 To celebrate, sit back, relax, and enjoy Yuto’s recently dubbed “Battle Commander” part and go congratulate him for becoming the World Champion!! 🏆🇯🇵 #skateboardingisfun #berrics

node.text: Its @alexmidler’s 23rd birthday today! 🥳 With all that he’s done at The Berrics (and all around the world), it’s hard to believe that he’s only 23 years old. Make sure you go wish Alex a very special Happy Birthday and be on the lookout for his #BATB12 game premiering this weekend! Happy Birthday Midler!! 🎂🎁 #skateboardingisfun #berrics

node.text: But one more thing!… if a 64 man bracket wasn’t insane enough, for the first time in skate history, we're going to find out which CEOs of big name action sports beverages are actually the best at skating! Who do you got?!👇 #skateboardingisfun #berrics
